47
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:46,870
Why didn't you mention it?

48
00:01:48,070 --> 00:01:49,510
I didn't know either.

49
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:50,760
Wait.

50
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,640
Will he really give you that much money?

51
00:01:54,430 --> 00:01:55,280
Not chicken wings?

52
00:01:56,310 --> 00:01:57,200
Listen up, everyone.

53
00:01:58,310 --> 00:01:59,400
He wouldn't dare refuse now.

54
00:02:00,790 --> 00:02:03,280
He's afraid his precious son finds out.

55
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,480
Three million!

56
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:09,560
I wouldn't see that much money
in eight lifetimes!

57
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:11,750
Man, truth be told,

58
00:02:12,430 --> 00:02:15,150
I think three million is too little.

59
00:02:16,310 --> 00:02:16,800
What?

60
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:19,190
How so?

61
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:23,240
Whatever historical issues aside,

62
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:24,910
you're his real son, right?

63
00:02:25,420 --> 00:02:26,220
Yes.

64
00:02:26,870 --> 00:02:28,910
Then you and that official heir of his

65
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,470
should have equal status.

66
00:02:31,030 --> 00:02:32,000
By all accounts

67
00:02:32,590 --> 00:02:35,000
your rich dad's money should be split

68
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:35,680
fifty-fifty.

69
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:36,240
No, no.

70
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,080
Dude,

71
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,800
three mil is plenty of money!

72
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:40,630
It's more than you can spend
for a lifetime!

73
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:41,960
Look how small-minded you are!

74
00:02:42,590 --> 00:02:43,310
Man, listen to me.

75
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,190
He's trying to hush things up now

76
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:47,470
not just because
he fears his son will find out.

77
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:49,710
He's definitely scared
you'll demand more.

78
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,400
Think about it, makes sense right?

79
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:59,080
I'm just too kind-hearted!

80
00:02:59,360 --> 00:02:59,840
Exactly!

81
00:03:00,470 --> 00:03:01,430
Dear father,

82
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,960
looks like three million won't be enough.

83
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:08,120
You'll need to compensate me more.

84
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:10,680
You make a pretty good point!

85
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:11,400
Here.

86
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:11,960
Cheers.

87
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:13,080
Drink.

88
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:44,590
Wow.

89
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:45,310
Humidifier?

90
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:48,030
No wonder it didn't feel so dry today.

91
00:03:49,140 --> 00:03:50,680
Hey.

92
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:51,910
The logistics department went all out.

93
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,240
Logistics?

94
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:56,470
What are you thinking?

95
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:57,560
It's not in their budget.

96
00:03:58,020 --> 00:03:58,940
Huh?

97
00:03:59,630 --> 00:04:00,800
Then where's this humidifier from

98
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:04,000
The lady who
came to our ward three months ago,

99
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:06,120
the one who later
passed from lung infection,

100
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:06,800
remember her?

101
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:08,840
She has a son.

102
00:04:08,870 --> 00:04:10,240
He's tall and handsome.

103
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,840
Heard he's some business owner.

104
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,870
Mr. Ai. Do you know him?

105
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,310
To show gratitude

106
00:04:17,310 --> 00:04:18,950
for our care of his mother,

107
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,240
he donated a humidifier to every office

108
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,360
in the Rehabilitation Department

109
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,800
Who's he really doing this for?

110
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:27,950
I don't believe
he has no ulterior motive.

111
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:32,980
Hey,

112
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:33,950
Wu Ya.

113
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,000
Is he the one

114
00:04:36,390 --> 00:04:38,430
who sent you flowers before?

115
00:04:51,390 --> 00:04:51,800
What?

116
00:04:52,430 --> 00:04:53,800
You're applying for hospital dormitory?

117
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:54,480
Why?

118
00:04:56,310 --> 00:04:57,800
Keeping some distance between two people

119
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,430
is good for relationship development.

120
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:01,270
Helps maintain novelty, too.

121
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:03,360
Tell me the truth.

122
00:05:03,830 --> 00:05:05,160
Are you saving money to get married?

123
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:07,680
It must be.

124
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,310
Living alone,

125
00:05:09,870 --> 00:05:11,390
he can rent a smaller place, right?

126
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,510
Ms. Duan, please stop asking.

127
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:17,000
I want to move in as soon as possible.

128
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:18,800
Please put in a good word fro me.

129
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,310
Alright, I understand.

130
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:23,480
It's ready.

131
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:24,950
Eight seconds, right?

132
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:26,510
Here's one for you.

133
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,390
Eight.

134
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:31,920
Seven.

135
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:33,720
Six.

136
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:35,600
Five.

137
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:36,560
Xiaozhou.

138
00:05:37,390 --> 00:05:39,270
I'm moving into the hospital dormitory.

139
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,920
Since our lease
is about to expire anyway,

140
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,310
I was thinking

141
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,800
we could switch to a smaller place.

142
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,720
No, you...you don't have to.

143
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:54,310
It's not like I'm being considerate.

144
00:05:54,870 --> 00:05:55,950
It's just my department...

145
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:57,390
What about it?

146
00:05:58,360 --> 00:06:00,630
You know how my
overtime keeps increasing.

147
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:03,310
My daily commute takes 1-2 hours,

148
00:06:03,510 --> 00:06:05,190
and traffic jams make it unpredictable.

149
00:06:05,750 --> 00:06:07,000
Several times,

150
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:08,950
I was late for morning rounds.

151
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:11,120
The director didn't look happy.

152
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:13,800
Should we maybe

153
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:15,600
move closer to the hospital?

154
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:18,160
The director suggested it to me.

155
00:06:18,430 --> 00:06:19,480
Said there's an available bed

156
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:20,390
and asked me to consider it.

157
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,120
I can't play dumb, can I?

158
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,040
I see...

159
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,310
It's way over eight seconds.

160
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:32,950
Eat it.

161
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,800
Overcooked? Let me make you a fresh one.

162
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:36,360
Here.

163
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:40,680
Eight.

164
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,560
Why do I feel like

165
00:06:45,630 --> 00:06:46,750
I'm being abandoned?

166
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,120
Exactly.

167
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,920
I'm climbing the social ladder
and dumping you.

168
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:52,630
Don't you dare be so dramatic.

169
00:06:53,390 --> 00:06:54,750
You can't joke about such things.

170
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:56,560
Don't scare me.

171
00:06:58,270 --> 00:06:59,360
Just kidding.

172
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:03,480
Here, it's ready.

173
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:06,600
Have something light.

174
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:52,360
Dad.

175
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:54,630
During my trip to France,

176
00:07:54,630 --> 00:07:56,390
I met some young contemporary artists.

177
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,070
They're quite interested in

178
00:07:59,070 --> 00:08:00,070
entering the Chinese market.

179
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:02,190
So,

180
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:03,750
my initial plan is

181
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:05,630
maybe after this June,

182
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,360
I'll get their representative works

183
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:09,480
and see if we can organize an exhibition.

184
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:11,480
Good.

185
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,360
You handle it.

186
00:08:16,510 --> 00:08:16,830
Dad.

187
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,560
Any instructions?

188
00:08:18,950 --> 00:08:19,800
What should I do first?

189
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,680
No special instructions.

190
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:26,510
The company affairs are yours now.

191
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:27,950
You make the decisions.

192
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:31,950
Thanks, Dad.

193
00:08:33,630 --> 00:08:34,480
I'll get back to work.

194
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:35,790
Everything alright?

195
00:08:35,940 --> 00:08:36,380
Yes.

196
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:46,240
Dad.

197
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,630
Why is one of Qin's paintings missing?

198
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:49,550
You put it away?

199
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:56,550
I,

200
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:58,510
I thought

201
00:09:00,910 --> 00:09:02,030
I could put up another painting

202
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:03,720
for a change of mood.

203
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:05,220
Oh.

204
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,360
In that case,

205
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,240
I can take it back for you.

206
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,360
The preservation conditions here

207
00:09:08,630 --> 00:09:09,670
might not meet the requirements.

208
00:09:10,630 --> 00:09:12,000
It's perfectly safe here.

209
00:09:12,870 --> 00:09:14,840
I'll have someone hang it
in the bedroom this afternoon.

210
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:15,670
I'm right here.

211
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:16,840
Why ask someone else?

212
00:09:16,870 --> 00:09:17,390
I'll do it.

213
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,750
I need to take a nap.

214
00:09:24,550 --> 00:09:25,120
Off you go.

215
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:27,440
Sure, Dad.

216
00:09:27,910 --> 00:09:28,200
Okay.

217
00:09:39,390 --> 00:09:39,870
Who are you?

218
00:09:43,220 --> 00:09:43,550
Hey!

219
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:44,200
I'm talking to you!

220
00:09:44,860 --> 00:09:45,270
Hey!

221
00:09:45,270 --> 00:09:45,910
Mr. Ai.

222
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:47,390
Stop right there. Who are you?

223
00:09:49,910 --> 00:09:50,550
Dad, you know him?

224
00:09:52,630 --> 00:09:53,750
Sorry, this is a private club.

225
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,270
Hey, Mr. Ai, are we in the wrong place?

226
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:57,360
Get out!

227
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:05,320
Hey, look!

228
00:10:05,510 --> 00:10:05,870
What?

229
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:07,440
Do we two look alike?

230
00:10:09,030 --> 00:10:09,550
No.

231
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:10,670
Yes.

232
00:10:10,870 --> 00:10:11,200
Man,

233
00:10:11,390 --> 00:10:12,000
it's unbelievable!

234
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:13,390
You're just like twins.

235
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:15,600
What are you doing?

236
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:23,480
Dad.

237
00:10:25,910 --> 00:10:26,390
You know him?

238
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,550
The three days aren't up yet.

239
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:31,870
Why are here?

240
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:34,910
Three million is too little.

241
00:10:36,790 --> 00:10:37,750
Then how much do you want?

242
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,000
How much can he get?

243
00:10:42,630 --> 00:10:43,320
I want the same.

244
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:43,910
What did you say?

245
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:46,440
Dad, who is he?

246
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,870
Okay, you can leave for now.

247
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:50,790
Hey, Dad.

248
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,200
Your son's talking to you.

249
00:10:52,550 --> 00:10:53,480
I said leave.

250
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:54,120
Go.

251
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,030
Alright?

252
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:55,840
Dad.

253
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:56,670
Dad, who is he really?

254
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,240
Tell him.

255
00:10:58,510 --> 00:11:00,240
Having another brother is a good thing.

256
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,240
If you keep talking.

257
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:03,030
I'll make sure you get nothing.

258
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,080
You hear me?

259
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:04,790
Leave.

260
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:05,200
No, wait.

261
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:05,720
I said get out!

262
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:06,150
No.

263
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:06,750
Well.

264
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,790
You won't talk? Then I will.

265
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:11,390
Your dad is my dad too.

266
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:11,960
Ma Xiao...

267
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,270
After college, he was assigned to

268
00:11:13,390 --> 00:11:15,030
the cultural center
in my mom's hometown.

269
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:16,270
He dated my mom.

270
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,720
- Ma Xiaowei. -She then had me!

271
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:18,360
Don't listen...

272
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,320
Later your mom

273
00:11:19,390 --> 00:11:20,270
- Don't listen. - went painting.

274
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:20,840
Don't listen to him.

275
00:11:21,030 --> 00:11:21,750
When our dad saw

276
00:11:22,030 --> 00:11:23,440
your grandpa had power and influence,

277
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:25,000
- he wanted the big city! - Ma Xiaowei!

278
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:25,870
- Ma Xiaowei! - Then later,

279
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,390
he abandoned my mom!

280
00:11:27,390 --> 00:11:28,200
Ma Xiaowei!

281
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,120
Ridiculous right?

282
00:11:30,550 --> 00:11:31,750
Get out now!

283
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:33,150
Out!

284
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:38,550
Is what he said true?

285
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:41,360
Let me explain okay?

286
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,600
-Let me explain. -Dad, Dad.

287
00:11:43,790 --> 00:11:44,200
Okay?

288
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:47,870
Since my brother is here today,

289
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:49,720
let's lay all cards on the table.

290
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:52,320
Why does he get to live large,

291
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:55,000
while my mom just gets
a few thousands yearly?

292
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:00,600
You kept in touch with them.

293
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:02,840
