00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:21,880
Are you trying to kill Mr. Ai?

588
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:22,880
What are you saying?

589
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:25,310
He's your boss's real son!

590
00:27:25,510 --> 00:27:26,510
You dare drive us away?

591
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:28,590
Hear that? Xiaowei says no treatment.

592
00:27:28,590 --> 00:27:28,830
Right.

593
00:27:28,830 --> 00:27:29,310
Find someone!

594
00:27:29,510 --> 00:27:30,640
Get Mr. Ai discharged!

595
00:27:30,790 --> 00:27:31,270
Doctor.

596
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:32,480
Can you treat him first?

597
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:34,200
Family will sign when they arrive.

598
00:27:35,070 --> 00:27:35,440
Well...

599
00:27:37,070 --> 00:27:38,070
It's a matter of life and death.

600
00:27:38,790 --> 00:27:40,030
Doctor, let me tell you.

601
00:27:40,590 --> 00:27:41,510
You can't treat recklessly.

602
00:27:41,830 --> 00:27:43,160
If anything goes wrong,

603
00:27:43,510 --> 00:27:44,440
you'll be held responsible.

604
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:44,720
Right.

605
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:45,720
Ma Xiaowei, you bastard!

606
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:46,590
What are you doing?

607
00:27:46,590 --> 00:27:47,160
Hit me?

608
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:47,960
Stop it!

609
00:27:48,070 --> 00:27:49,030
What are you all doing?

610
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:52,270
Stop arguing! Quiet! This is a hospital!

611
00:27:52,350 --> 00:27:53,110
Don't fight!

612
00:27:53,110 --> 00:27:53,960
Stop fighting!

613
00:27:54,350 --> 00:27:55,110
What's all the noise?

614
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:55,750
What are you doing?

615
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:56,590
No fighting!

616
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:58,110
Doctor, I'll sign.

617
00:27:58,270 --> 00:27:59,030
I'm Ai Zhonghua's son.

618
00:28:00,030 --> 00:28:00,680
What are you doing?

619
00:28:01,110 --> 00:28:01,720
Why are you here?

620
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:02,640
I'm signing it.

621
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:03,680
Go back.

622
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:04,270
What are you doing?

623
00:28:04,350 --> 00:28:05,350
How dare you come here?

624
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:05,960
What are you doing?

625
00:28:05,960 --> 00:28:07,720
My dad became like this because of you!

626
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:09,350
And now you come to sign this thing.

627
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,720
I think you're
deliberately trying to kill him!

628
00:28:11,790 --> 00:28:12,200
Right.

629
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:13,640
I did this to him?

630
00:28:14,070 --> 00:28:15,920
Ma Xiaowei,
we'll settle our score later!

631
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:16,960
Right now I'm here to sign this!

632
00:28:17,270 --> 00:28:17,750
No way!

633
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:19,030
Sign it, I dare you.

634
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:19,880
Listen up everyone

635
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:21,480
Nobody harms my father.

636
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:22,640
I'll stand guard here today.

637
00:28:22,750 --> 00:28:24,030
If I say no treatment, then no treatment.

638
00:28:24,110 --> 00:28:24,550
Exactly.

639
00:28:24,720 --> 00:28:25,310
Stop it!

640
00:28:26,110 --> 00:28:26,960
This is a hospital!

641
00:28:27,510 --> 00:28:28,510
We won't tolerate your nonsense!

642
00:28:29,070 --> 00:28:30,480
Family disputes, is it?

643
00:28:30,830 --> 00:28:31,960
Take it outside!

644
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:32,830
Let me tell you.

645
00:28:33,440 --> 00:28:35,880
Now is the critical recovery period.

646
00:28:36,070 --> 00:28:37,240
Miss this window,

647
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:38,550
you face the consequences!

648
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:40,270
Move aside!

649
00:28:42,510 --> 00:28:43,440
This is ridiculous!

650
00:28:44,270 --> 00:28:44,750
What?

651
00:28:45,270 --> 00:28:45,830
What now?

652
00:28:45,830 --> 00:28:46,350
Bring it on.

653
00:28:46,790 --> 00:28:47,680
Mr. Ai, calm down!

654
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:48,200
Wanna fight?

655
00:28:50,550 --> 00:28:51,750
Calm down, Mr. Ai.

656
00:28:52,750 --> 00:28:53,350
Ma Xiaowei.

657
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,920
You'd better pray that Mr. Ai

658
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:56,920
can wake up.

659
00:28:57,720 --> 00:28:58,640
What do you mean by that?

660
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:00,200
He's my biological father

661
00:29:00,590 --> 00:29:01,880
Of course I want him healthy.

662
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:02,680
And safe and sound.

663
00:29:02,830 --> 00:29:03,590
No, you don't.

664
00:29:04,030 --> 00:29:05,440
You want something bad to happen,

665
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:06,920
so you can get half the fortune.

666
00:29:07,030 --> 00:29:07,750
You... you...

667
00:29:08,270 --> 00:29:09,200
Don't talk nonsense.

668
00:29:09,550 --> 00:29:10,400
That's your assumption.

669
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:11,310
I never meant that!

670
00:29:11,510 --> 00:29:13,440
Your clever scheme isn't wrong.

671
00:29:14,070 --> 00:29:14,960
But if things really

672
00:29:14,960 --> 00:29:16,400
come to that point.

673
00:29:16,790 --> 00:29:18,790
You'll need to prove your relation
with Mr. Ai.

674
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:20,350
Right? What will you need?

675
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:21,590
A DNA test.

676
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:22,480
To run a DNA test,

677
00:29:22,750 --> 00:29:24,030
you need Mr. Ai Linjiang's approval.

678
00:29:24,510 --> 00:29:25,350
If he disagrees,

679
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:26,160
you can't get tested.

680
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:30,750
Listen, don't try to scare me.

681
00:29:31,160 --> 00:29:31,880
You're his man.

682
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:32,640
You side with him.

683
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:34,110
I graduated from law school.

684
00:29:34,110 --> 00:29:35,160
If you don't believe me,

685
00:29:35,160 --> 00:29:36,070
we can make a bet

686
00:29:36,310 --> 00:29:38,400
to see if I'm telling the truth.

687
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:41,400
You'd better pray Mr. Ai stays safe.

688
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:42,720
And in good health

689
00:29:43,350 --> 00:29:43,960
When he's awake,

690
00:29:44,070 --> 00:29:45,510
he might still spare you some change

691
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:47,070
for your mother's sake.

692
00:29:47,550 --> 00:29:49,270
Otherwise, you won't get a single cent.

693
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:53,640
Xiaowei.

694
00:29:57,750 --> 00:29:58,270
Alright.

695
00:29:58,270 --> 00:29:59,030
Sign if you want to.

696
00:29:59,270 --> 00:30:00,240
Do whatever you please.

697
00:30:00,750 --> 00:30:02,240
But let me make this clear.

698
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:04,960
If anything happens to my father,

699
00:30:05,310 --> 00:30:07,000
I won't let you off the hook. Let's go!

700
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:08,510
Just you wait!

701
00:30:10,510 --> 00:30:11,720
Call the doctor! We'll sign.

702
00:30:12,110 --> 00:30:12,480
Okay.

703
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:18,750
It's already dawn.

704
00:30:22,400 --> 00:30:24,240
How did you finally convince
Ai Linjiang?

705
00:30:26,110 --> 00:30:26,680
I'll never know

706
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,270
what my father wanted to tell me
before he died.

707
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:30,110
Even just an "I'm sorry"

708
00:30:30,110 --> 00:30:31,270
or calling me "son" once.

709
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:33,200
I might

710
00:30:35,590 --> 00:30:37,030
not have suffered this much.

711
00:30:39,310 --> 00:30:39,830
Mr. Ai.

712
00:30:41,510 --> 00:30:41,960
Don't you

713
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:45,000
want to hear your father

714
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:47,510
tell you the truth himself?

715
00:30:54,030 --> 00:30:55,510
Your story is moving,

716
00:30:58,070 --> 00:30:59,070
but it doesn't move me.

717
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:01,960
The truth is already clear.

718
00:31:02,590 --> 00:31:03,310
My father,

719
00:31:04,310 --> 00:31:05,240
for all these years,

720
00:31:05,830 --> 00:31:07,350
has kept ties with his first love,

721
00:31:07,590 --> 00:31:09,160
even with shady dealings

722
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:10,200
I didn't know about.

723
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:12,480
What if he maintained contact

724
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:13,830
out of responsibility?

725
00:31:15,680 --> 00:31:16,720
Don't speak for him.

726
00:31:17,550 --> 00:31:18,440
I'm not speaking for him.

727
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:20,070
When I first heard Mr. Ai's story,

728
00:31:20,160 --> 00:31:20,960
I thought it was fake too.

729
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:21,880
I thought he made it up.

730
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:24,680
It thought it was to
make excuses for himself.

731
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:25,510
I was furious too.

732
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:28,440
But I'm just an outsider.

733
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:30,400
I know nothing.

734
00:31:31,750 --> 00:31:32,590
Only you know

735
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:35,790
whether he played
the perfect husband and father

736
00:31:35,790 --> 00:31:36,480
for 30 years,

737
00:31:37,510 --> 00:31:38,160
or

738
00:31:38,880 --> 00:31:41,030
he genuinely cared for you both.

739
00:31:41,790 --> 00:31:43,720
Only you know the truth, Mr. Ai.

740
00:31:53,790 --> 00:31:54,400
Let me ask you.

741
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:58,440
What if it's really as I suspect?

742
00:31:58,720 --> 00:31:59,960
Then go hear his confession.

743
00:32:00,310 --> 00:32:01,790
Even the most wicked villain

744
00:32:01,790 --> 00:32:02,880
deserves the right to repent.

745
00:32:04,350 --> 00:32:06,510
Seriously, Mr. Ai, don't end up like me.

746
00:32:07,270 --> 00:32:07,960
In the days to come,

747
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:09,880
you'll keep thinking over and over

748
00:32:11,720 --> 00:32:13,270
about the days you spent together.

749
00:32:13,270 --> 00:32:14,160
Were they real

750
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:16,070
or just fake?

751
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:19,790
Take my advice.

752
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:21,240
Go to the hospital.

753
00:32:22,720 --> 00:32:23,400
Listen to Mr. Ai.

754
00:32:26,160 --> 00:32:27,200
Let him explain.

755
00:32:29,030 --> 00:32:30,030
Don't regret it for life.

756
00:32:35,750 --> 00:32:36,510
Not bad.

757
00:32:37,030 --> 00:32:37,720
You've improved.

758
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:40,830
Mainly thanks to what you said.

759
00:32:42,480 --> 00:32:43,000
Really?

760
00:32:43,750 --> 00:32:45,350
I've said so many reasonable things.

761
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:46,830
Which one?

762
00:32:48,640 --> 00:32:49,310
The one about

763
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:51,790
apologies needing to be reclaimed.

764
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:54,550
Have you reclaimed yours?

765
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:55,310
Me?

766
00:32:56,590 --> 00:32:57,270
Still working on it.

767
00:32:58,070 --> 00:32:58,640
Not that fast.

768
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:07,200
I'm back.

769
00:33:09,900 --> 00:33:10,540
Yes.

770
00:33:17,270 --> 00:33:18,030
Baodan.

771
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:22,310
What are you doing?

772
00:33:23,590 --> 00:33:24,350
Looking for something.

773
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:27,880
Looking for what?

774
00:34:00,270 --> 00:34:02,110
Ya, you asked me before.

775
00:34:03,110 --> 00:34:04,160
After my mom had the accident

776
00:34:05,350 --> 00:34:07,200
if I regretted
dropping out to care for her.

777
00:34:10,710 --> 00:34:11,710
Why bring this up suddenly?

778
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,320
Everyone thinks I did it

779
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:16,230
because I'm a good son.

780
00:34:18,960 --> 00:34:19,710
But actually no.

781
00:34:21,190 --> 00:34:22,320
I didn't do it for my mom,

782
00:34:24,550 --> 00:34:26,440
or not entirely for her.

783
00:34:28,510 --> 00:34:29,760
Mostly I did it for myself.

784
00:34:31,280 --> 00:34:32,190
For yourself?

785
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:38,030
After my dad passed away,

786
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:41,320
I felt so much pain.

787
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:44,280
To put it simply,

788
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:45,960
I was utterly devastated.

789
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:46,550
I felt like

790
00:34:47,280 --> 00:34:48,550
I had nothing left.

791
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:52,630
I had to exhaust myself

792
00:34:54,030 --> 00:34:55,360
by taking care of my mom

793
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:58,880
just to forget the pain.

794
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,710
I was using this to numb myself.

795
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:03,320
Otherwise,

796
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:05,070
I might have...

797
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:06,400
Xiaozhou,

798
00:35:09,630 --> 00:35:11,070
even though you keep saying

799
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,110
You won't forgive your father,

800
00:35:15,670 --> 00:35:16,880
you actually love him dearly.

801
00:35:17,800 --> 00:35:18,230
Don't you?

802
00:35:36,150 --> 00:35:37,000
My dad asked someone

803
00:35:38,150 --> 00:35:40,510
to buy me is game console from Japan.

804
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:42,230
After he bought it,

805
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:43,550
we both became

806
00:35:43,550 --> 00:35:45,840
totally addicted to this racing game.

807
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:46,920
We played it every single day,

808
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:47,760
day and night.

809
00:35:48,320 --> 00:35:49,400
Later because of this,

810
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:50,440
my mom kept scolding my dad.

811
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:51,440
But dad always protected me.

812
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:52,840
They went back and forth.

813
00:35:53,590 --> 00:35:54,190
Anyway...

814
00:35:56,440 --> 00:35:57,280
It was pretty happy times.

815
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:05,760
But soon after, they separated.

816
00:36:19,150 --> 00:36:19,670
What?

817
00:36:21,070 --> 00:36:22,280
Test if it still works.

818
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:24,070
It's been so long.

819
00:36:24,070 --> 00:36:24,880
Probably won't work.

820
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:26,110
Just give it a try.

821
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:36,920
Here, hold this.

822
00:36:38,030 --> 00:36:38,510
Take it.

823
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:40,760
Steady.

824
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:50,840
Careful.

825
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:08,960
It still works.

826
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:17,510
What?

827
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:18,550
I'll play with you.

828
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:23,360
No...never mind.

829
00:37:27,230 --> 00:37:28,800
Consider it remembering your dad.

830
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:46,460
Wait.

831
00:37:47,150 --> 00:37:47,550
What's wrong?

832
00:37:48,030 --> 00:37:48,670
Wait a minute.

833
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:51,550
Your parents split up 13 years ago.

834
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:54,920
But this game's last login was

835
00:37:54,920 --> 00:37:56,150
three years ago.

836
00:37:58,000 --> 00:37:59,070
On your birthday.

837
00:38:13,190 --> 00:38:13,670
Xiaozhou.

838
00:38:15,150 --> 00:38:15,960
I guess

839
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:18,000
after your parents separated,

840
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:19,670
every year on your birthday,

841
00:38:20,960 --> 00:38:22,510
your dad would launch this game.

842
00:38:24,400 --> 00:38:25,880
He was using this method

843
00:38:27,510 --> 00:38:28,400
to quietly think of you.

844
00:39:20,710 --> 00:39:21,800
I'm waiving inheritance rights

845
00:39:23,070 --> 00:39:24,070
to that apartment.

846
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:25,440
The agreement.

847
00:39:27,510 --> 00:39:28,070
Xiaozhou.

848
00:39:29,590 --> 00:39:30,630
Thank you for understanding

849
00:39:32,070 --> 00:39:32,670
Once I receive

850
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:34,550
the down payment, I'll transfer

851
00:39:34,590 --> 00:39:35,440
the 500K immediately.

852
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:35,880
No need.

853
00:39:36,670 --> 00:39:37,920
Wait till the company turns profit.

854
00:39:42,230 --> 00:39:44,190
I'm not selling for the money.

855
00:39:46,550 --> 00:39:47,150
My dad...

856
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:54,480
Anyway, the sale proceeds

857
00:39:55,480 --> 00:39:56,880
must go to company operations.

858
00:39:57,510 --> 00:39:59,110
This is clearly stated in the agreement.

859
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:01,590
After the transaction,

860
00:40:02,190 --> 00:40:03,840
I'll show you transfer proof.

861
00:40:21,880 --> 00:40:23,670
Get the contract notarized by lawyer.

862
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:25,590
Then arrange sale immediately.

863
00:40:26,190 --> 00:40:27,360
This needs urgent handling

864
00:40:28,070 --> 00:40:28,800
before he changes his mind.

865
00:40:29,630 --> 00:40:30,000
Alright.

866
00:40:30,510 --> 00:40:30,920
by the way

867
00:40:31,710 --> 00:40:33,150
is everything arranged with Li Fendou?

868
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:33,960
It's all scheduled.

869
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:36,150
But what if Professor Ding
doesn't cooperate?

870
00:40:37,030 --> 00:40:37,510
He will.

871
00:40:38,320 --> 00:40:39,110
He's a scholar.

872
00:40:39,760 --> 00:40:41,230
What scholars want is respect.

873
00:40:41,840 --> 00:40:43,320
As long as we show enough respect,

874
00:40:44,030 --> 00:40:44,510
he'll give us

875
00:40:45,110 --> 00:40:45,670
whatever we want.

876
00:40:59,630 --> 00:41:00,030
Thank you.

877
00:41:03,110 --> 00:41:04,630
Just a small 42nd birthday party.

878
00:41:04,710 --> 00:41:05,880
Some noodles at home would suffice.

879
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:06,760
Why must we go out?

880
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:08,920
This is the first birthday

881
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:10,360
we celebrate together.

882
00:41:10,880 --> 00:41:12,030
You have to follow my arrangements.

883
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:13,110
No objections allowed.

884
00:41:13,550 --> 00:41:14,800
Isn't this Li Fendou's place?

885
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:15,590
Why are we here?

886
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:16,840
Ms. Qiu!

887
00:41:17,360 --> 00:41:17,960
Mr. Li!

888
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:19,960
I didn't know you are today.

889
00:41:21,480 --> 00:41:22,880
Just finished a lunch meeting.

890
00:41:24,630 --> 00:41:25,510
And this is?

891
00:41:26,710 --> 00:41:27,630
Let me introduce you.

892
00:41:28,030 --> 00:41:29,630
This is my partner, Ding Zhiyuan.

893
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:30,320
Hello.

894
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:31,710
Professor Ding!

895
00:41:32,590 --> 00:41:33,000
Hello!

896
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,280
I've long heard of your reputation.

897
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:36,510
I contacted you the other day.

898
00:41:36,670 --> 00:41:38,000
Ms. Qiu said you're busy.

899
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:38,550
But look!

900
00:41:38,920 --> 00:41:40,000
I caught you red-handed today!

901
00:41:40,760 --> 00:41:43,070
As they say, planned meetings
aren't as good as chance encounters.

902
00:41:43,360 --> 00:41:44,630
Let's have a proper drink today, okay?

903
00:41:44,960 --> 00:41:45,320
Allow me!

904
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:46,710
That won't do.

905
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:49,150
Today is Professor Ding's birthday.

906
00:41:49,510 --> 00:41:50,880
Don't you dare steal my guest.

907
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:53,320
Birthday, huh?

908
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:54,280
Perfect.

909
00:41:54,920 --> 00:41:56,280
Wang, come here!

910
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:57,280
Coming!

911
00:41:58,480 --> 00:42:00,150
Clear out the best private room for me.

912
00:42:00,590 --> 00:42:01,920
And order the finest cake.

913
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:03,190
It must arrive within half an hour.

914
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:04,590
Yes, Mr. Li.

915
00:42:05,510 --> 00:42:06,880
Mr. Li, really, there's no need.

916
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:08,710
Professor Ding...

917
00:42:09,510 --> 00:42:10,070
I understand.

918
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:13,360
Birthdays should be for couples' time.

919
00:42:13,840 --> 00:42:15,630
But I must show my respect.

920
00:42:16,110 --> 00:42:17,960
Don't worry,
I'll leave after arranging everything.

921
00:42:18,150 --> 00:42:18,710
Won't be in the way.

922
00:42:19,670 --> 00:42:20,710
How could we accept this?

923
00:42:21,110 --> 00:42:23,110
Exactly. You're the host treating us.

924
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:25,440
Guests shouldn't make the host leave.

925
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:26,800
That'll be inappropriate.

926
00:42:28,710 --> 00:42:29,630
Mr. Li, how about...

927
00:42:30,190 --> 00:42:30,630
You...

928
00:42:31,710 --> 00:42:32,320
Join us?

929
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:34,360
Ms. Qiu.

930
00:42:34,960 --> 00:42:37,510
I shouldn't be a third wheel.

931
00:42:37,550 --> 00:42:38,590
Don't be silly.

932
00:42:38,880 --> 00:42:40,360
We'll have plenty of couple time.

933
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:42,320
Right, Zhiyuan?

934
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:44,710
Right.

935
00:42:45,190 --> 00:42:45,630
Yes.

936
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:46,630
See?

937
00:42:47,030 --> 00:42:47,880
Let's eat together.

938
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:49,550
That'd be wonderful!

939
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:51,150
If Professor Ding doesn't mind,

940
00:42:51,670 --> 00:42:52,670
let's celebrate together!

941
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:54,150
Tea first, alright?

942
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:54,710
Alright!

943
00:42:54,710 --> 00:42:55,150
Here.

944
00:42:55,150 --> 00:42:56,400
Let's go.

945
00:43:06,720 --> 00:43:08,600
♪If I close both eyes tonight♪

946
00:43:08,600 --> 00:43:12,480
♪Back to that wishing summer night♪

947
00:43:12,480 --> 00:43:16,240
♪Wind brushes your shaking frame♪

948
00:43:16,240 --> 00:43:21,040
♪That world feels close just the same♪

949
00:43:21,040 --> 00:43:23,440
♪If I dare to face the dawn♪

950
00:43:23,440 --> 00:43:27,160
♪Do you know this face you'd drawn♪

951
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:30,960
♪Gray spirals looped in endless chase♪

952
00:43:30,960 --> 00:43:35,760
♪Tracing tears not words they trace♪

953
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:38,520
♪How many times must this repeat♪

954
00:43:38,520 --> 00:43:42,040
♪Sighs pull my gaze to retreat♪

955
00:43:42,040 --> 00:43:45,880
♪Sleepless nights, risks untold♪

956
00:43:45,880 --> 00:43:50,680
♪None of it for my own soul♪

957
00:43:50,680 --> 00:43:52,120
♪Winds blew, rains poured♪

958
00:43:52,120 --> 00:43:54,000
♪Umbrellas broke, we soared♪

959
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:56,080
♪Sky fell, ground shook♪

960
00:43:56,080 --> 00:43:57,600
♪Through dusk till dawn I stood♪

961
00:43:57,600 --> 00:43:59,560
♪Cars passed, dreams drowned♪

962
00:43:59,560 --> 00:44:04,960
♪Every stop's chain unbound♪

963
00:44:04,960 --> 00:44:07,000
♪Moon watched, stars blazed♪

964
00:44:07,000 --> 00:44:08,880
♪Lamps died, connections phased♪

965
00:44:08,880 --> 00:44:11,000
♪Held hands, laughed then cried♪

966
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:12,280
♪Hearts froze, parts died inside♪

967
00:44:12,280 --> 00:44:14,920
♪Tried hard, spoke true♪

968
00:44:14,920 --> 00:44:16,920
♪Now I'm someone I never knew♪

969
00:44:20,040 --> 00:44:21,920
♪Love came, hate stayed♪

970
00:44:21,920 --> 00:44:23,440
♪I arrived, you frayed♪

971
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:24,800
♪Voice cracked, tears burned♪

972
00:44:24,800 --> 00:44:26,800
♪Life lost, lessons earned♪

973
00:44:27,160 --> 00:44:29,400
♪Grew up, let go♪

974
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:31,400
♪Why cling to old sorrow♪

975
00:44:41,800 --> 00:44:44,760
♪How many loops replay♪

976
00:44:44,760 --> 00:44:48,440
♪Sighs steal my gaze away♪

977
00:44:48,440 --> 00:44:51,960
♪Lost nights, bold bets♪

978
00:44:51,960 --> 00:44:56,600
♪Nothing for my regrets♪

979
00:44:56,600 --> 00:45:01,000
♪Winds raged, storms crashed♪

980
00:45:01,000 --> 00:45:03,680
♪Dawns broke, I held fast♪

981
00:45:03,680 --> 00:45:05,800
♪Cars fled, dreams fled♪

982
00:45:05,800 --> 00:45:11,280
♪Every route left dead♪

983
00:45:11,280 --> 00:45:12,800
♪Love left, hate stayed♪

984
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:14,680
♪Voice gone, tears paid♪

985
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:18,320
♪Grew strong, moved on♪

986
00:45:18,320 --> 00:45:20,320
♪Why dwell when it's gone♪
